Schema Latex table¶

To rename a variable, please use the following template:

{
    'old':'XX',
    'new':'XX_1'
    }

if you need to pass a latex format with \, you need to duplicate it for instance, \text becomes `\text:

{
    'old':'working\_capital\_i',
    'new':'\\text{working capital}_i'
    }

Then add it to the key to_rename

Table 1: Pollution abatement channel¶

$$\begin{aligned} \text{Equipment}_{cit} &= \alpha_2 \text{Internal finance}_{cit-1}+\beta \text{X}_{cit} + \gamma_{it} +\gamma_{ct} + \epsilon_{cit} \end{aligned}$$

The following variables are lagged:

  • cashflow
  • current ratio
  • sale over asset

Gross change¶

Gross change is calculated as follow:

  • equipment t - equipment t-1
  • Augmentation du cashflow finance les investissements qui rduisent les SO2, mais pas le meme rsulat pour le current ratio, pourquoi?
  • Que mesure finalement la variable equipment -> est ce que les investissments dans les technos green ne sont mesurs que par la variable equipment.
  • Est ce que les descriptives stats sont correctes?
  • interaction: industry & industry-city
  • Que mesure prcisement SO2 equipment?
